### List the chat thread for an analysis
### Replace <PARENT_PROCESS_ID> with the processId of any analysis on the document
### (you can grab one from GET /documents/DOC-2026-04-000001)
GET http://localhost:3001/documents/DOC-2026-04-000001/messages?parentProcessId=<PARENT_PROCESS_ID>

### Ask a follow-up question about a document
### Same parentProcessId — the assistant will use that analysis as context.
POST http://localhost:3001/documents/DOC-2026-04-000001/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "parentProcessId": "<PARENT_PROCESS_ID>",
  "providerCode": "anthropic",
  "model": "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
  "question": "What is the total quantity ordered across all line items?"
}

### A second follow-up — the model gets the prior conversation as history
POST http://localhost:3001/documents/DOC-2026-04-000001/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "parentProcessId": "<PARENT_PROCESS_ID>",
  "providerCode": "anthropic",
  "model": "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
  "question": "Which of those products has the highest unit price?"
}
